    "body": "### Duplicate Check\n\n- [x] I confirm I searched for existing reports and found no duplicates.\n\n### Describe the Bug\n\nWhen logged in with a YouTube Music/Google account, the home screen shows duplicate or redundant \"Welcome back\" greetings/personalization cards one after another, which feels cluttered and unnecessary.\n\nWhat actually happens:\n- Top greeting: \"Good Evening\" (or time-based) + mood chips (All, Relax, etc.).  \n- Then: \"Welcome back,\" + profile card (e.g., \"A Ssvp\" with avatar/initial).  \n- Immediately below: Another \"Welcome back,\" + a second card like \"Welcome A\" (name-based).  \n\nThis creates a redundant double-welcome look that takes up extra vertical space and feels annoying/cluttered right on launch. It makes the otherwise beautiful UI feel messy.\n\nExpected: Only a single, clean personalized greeting or welcome section (or an option to hide it).\n\n### Steps to Reproduce\n\n1. Install SimpMusic (version 1.0.4, full arm64-v8a build).  \n2. Log in with a YouTube Music/Google account.  \n3. Open the app and go to the Home tab.\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nA single, clean personalized greeting or welcome section (or none at all if customizable). No duplication of \"Welcome back\" text/cards.\n\n### App Version\n\n1.0.4\n\n### Android Version\n\nAndroid 16\n\n### Device Model\n\nSamsung Galaxy S21FE (Exynos)\n\n### Custom ROM\n\n- [ ] I am using a custom ROM\n\n### Custom ROM Name (if applicable)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Screenshots (optional)\n\n![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/aa571d3c-e37f-467f-9812-6c4bd67b4bdb)\n\n### Log / Error Details\n\n_No response_",
